---------- git:

in order to initiate a git project
- enter the root projectt folder
- run

---------------------------- terminal--------------------------------------------

$ git init
Initialized empty Git repository in /actual-path-to-project-folder/.git/

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------

even if files are a√≤ready present in the folder the init returns empty folder
the files to monitor must be added.
in order to add all the files in the folder:

---------------------------- terminal--------------------------------------------

$ git status
On branch master

Initial commit

Untracked files:
  (use "git add <file>..." to include in what will be committed)

	#notes_about_git.txt#
	.#notes_about_git.txt
	index.html
	notes_about_git.txt

nothing added to commit but untracked files present (use "git add" to track)


